{"word":"ἄκαρπος","slug":"ἄκαρπος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄκαρπος</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without fruit, barren</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>fruitless, unprofitable</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-πως</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>making barren, blasting</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}